author: @Anthony_Gx
text:
You know what I really miss tho?? 
Lisa’s part post-Chorus, where she sings:

Jigeum nae ireumul bulleo 
Tell me I’ll be your deobul love 
I noraerul bulleo 
Tell me that you’ll be my geu love 

:( that was one of my favorite parts of that song. And Lisa’s rap in the newer/official version, is the only rap I don’t rlly feel. I love when Lisa raps. Her flow and swag is unique and I never mind if she gets a rap and Jennie just sings… but this rap feels   a bit hasted/rushed. A bit easy, not of actual BP quality. Especially now I compare it to her raps in PV and particularly in ShutDown… those raps are awesome. Perfect how it’s put together. The way it rhymes. But R4L rap is basically just a couple of sentences, spoken in the same tone. It’s not bad, just not very original/creative imo. 
I’d prefer her singing post-chorus 😢 

🤪 I still love and bought the album ofcourse tho!!🎉 I’ll listen to the old leaked version here on YT en basically we now have 2 songs for the price of 1: R4L from Born Pink and R4L leak. With jisoo also singing the verse 🤩 so no complaining. I just wanted to express how I liked that post chorus part and don’t understand why they cut that out. I also haven’t seen anyone else mentioning it, so I wonder if most pple didn’t notice it, or maybe others think it’s an improvement now that it’s taken out of the song??? 🤗
